1
00:00:03,110 --> 00:00:07,000
“Die to live” according to 
Guru Mahārāj means:

2
00:00:07,350 --> 00:00:10,924
you’ll have to die as you are

3
00:00:10,924 --> 00:00:15,914
to live, get life 
in a higher plane.

4
00:00:16,204 --> 00:00:18,274
[Self Generation]

5
00:00:18,868 --> 00:00:25,018
Yagya, the fire sacrifice, 
what was the idea? Is that …

6
00:00:27,702 --> 00:00:31,695
the self is thrown into the fire.

7
00:00:33,235 --> 00:00:40,705
That old self is disintegrated,
and a new self appears.

8
00:00:40,705 --> 00:00:44,985
The old self 
characterized by exploiting tendencies

9
00:00:44,985 --> 00:00:47,985
is disintegrated,

10
00:00:47,985 --> 00:00:52,993
and a new self 
characterized by dedicating tendency

11
00:00:52,993 --> 00:00:55,703
is generated
or, we can say,

12
00:00:55,703 --> 00:01:00,253
that dedicating tendency 
generates a new self.

13
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:04,307
Guru Mahārāj mentioned the conclusion

14
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:08,576
of perhaps Kalyāṇa-kalpataru,

15
00:01:08,576 --> 00:01:14,786
but where there’s Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur
talking about the nāma haṭṭa—

16
00:01:15,957 --> 00:01:20,697
the market of the Holy Name,
and Nityānanda Prabhu.

17
00:01:21,619 --> 00:01:28,279
This beautiful metaphor

18
00:01:28,279 --> 00:01:31,909
for distribution of Kṛṣṇa-nām.

19
00:01:31,909 --> 00:01:36,759
And Bhakti Vinod 􏰅Ṭhākur describes himself 
in that market of the Holy Name …

20
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:39,069
There’s Nityānanda Prabhu, 
the market of the Holy Name …

21
00:01:39,069 --> 00:01:44,439
He said, “And this Bhakti Vinod 
is a sweeper.”

22
00:01:45,385 --> 00:01:48,015
That’s his position there, 
he’s a sweeper.

23
00:01:48,015 --> 00:01:53,275
What is he sweeping out?
—Undesirable things.

24
00:01:54,766 --> 00:02:00,396
And Saraswatī Ṭhākur said,
“If that plane is so high,

25
00:02:00,734 --> 00:02:05,934
that in that plane 
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur is a sweeper,

26
00:02:06,208 --> 00:02:11,218
then I’m one of the straws 
in his broom.”

27
00:02:12,695 --> 00:02:14,555
And Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said,

28
00:02:14,555 --> 00:02:18,965
“If we take it that 
what he’s expressing

29
00:02:18,965 --> 00:02:23,535
is a sincere
heartfelt expression,

30
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:29,670
then you can understand 
the unitive construction of the svarūp.”

31
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:34,700
This type of humility 
and dedicating tendency

32
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:38,387
is the unit of construction
of the svarūp—

33
00:02:38,387 --> 00:02:44,817
of the spiritual form, 
identity, personality.

34
00:02:45,691 --> 00:02:50,111
So, however we can acquire 
dedicating tendency

35
00:02:50,706 --> 00:02:55,586
and association with our 
godbrothers and godsisters

36
00:02:55,586 --> 00:03:00,366
under the guidance of guru
and Vaiṣṇav,

37
00:03:01,302 --> 00:03:06,702
that ‘die to live’ principle 
can be employed.

38
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:12,549
The old self will disintegrate, 
the golden dedicating self will manifest.

